shared_text:
Community Free Library-Holley
August 14 at 7:06 PM ·

As you may have seen on the Orleans Hub last month, the county is installing WiFi hotspots throughout Orleans to increase internet access in our communities. The Holley Hotspot network is now up and running at the library! We've been informed that the signal at it's strongest should reach a 300 ft radius from it's location, meaning Internet can be used from this hotspot at Holley Gardens and throughout the village square, with decent signal available still outside of that. The network is open with no password. Next time you're nearby, connect to Holley Hotspot!

Community Free Library-Holley
August 14 at 5:35 PM ·

So much important information that we're sharing today! Approved by our Board of Trustees on August 13th, 2020, effective immediately, we will be temporarily closed Monday nights from 4-8 pm. We will remain open Wednesday nights from 4-8 pm. Normally, we reopen on Saturdays in September, but we are delaying that until at least October. This decision was made to accommodate the needs of our staff during this time. Thank you for understanding and being patient with us!

Full Address

shared_text:
Community Free Library-Holley
April 7 at 1:00 PM ·

Hi everyone,
Like many of you I was shaken by the Governor’s statement that we will stay closed down until May. I miss you all and truly wish I could help. All I can do is to remind you that if you have a library card -use it. Also, if you are having difficulty with WiFi, please go to the parking lot by the library and use our WiFi. I DID NOT TURN IT OFF. The password for Holley library public Is: HolleyLibrary. Please feel free to use it and all our databases.
May God keep you all healthy, until we can see each other again.

Sandy

post_text: Latest message from the Holley Community Free Library ...
shared_text:
Community Free Library-Holley
March 28 at 2:47 AM ·

Hi everyone, from what I gather from the Orleans legislature, they are looking at the schools and the library being closed until at least April 15th. But, they highly believe that it will be longer. So please do not worry about any of your items being overdue. When we open, all items will be checked in fine free so enjoy your books as long as you want to - read those story books many many times to the littles. Please, with everything to worry about - do not worry about the library- we are yours and we will do everything in our power to see you through these hard times. And as Lawrence Welk used to sing “Adios, Au Revoir, Auf Wedersehen “, goodnight!
Sandy

post_text: On August 10-11, the driveways and parking lots in the front and rear of Holley ES will be closed for sealing and repainting. The building will be accessible on Aug. 10, but cars will have to park at the former bus garage on High St. in order to walk to the building.

post_text:
Notice of Public Hearing on Holley Central School District's Code of Conduct and District Safety Plan

Please take notice that Holley Central School District will hold a public hearing on the district's Code of Conduct and District Safety Plan at its regular meeting on August 19, 2019, at 6 p.m. in the Board of Education Conference Room, located at 3800 North Main Street, Holley, NY. The district's proposed Code of Conduct and District Safety Plan are available for viewing during normal business hours at the District Office, located at 3800 North Main Street, Holley, NY.

Connie Nenni
District Clerk
